HEADWORD: Chirographist
<hw>Chi*rog"ra*phist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
chirographer; a writer or engrosser.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who tells fortunes by examining the
hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chirography</ent>⟦br⟧
